   If we choose $S_L$ or $S_R$ to be empty, their size is 0 and their XOR sum is 0. Our generation process must account for this. Since we iterate over all $2^{N/2}$ subsets, the empty set (XOR sum 0, size 0) will naturally be included in both maps.

